WEBVTT

00:02.369 --> 00:03.704
<i>PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i>ON "DEVIOUS MAIDS"...</i>

00:03.704 --> 00:05.439
ROSIE, I CANNOT GET OVER
HOW FAST HE'S TYPING.

00:05.439 --> 00:06.607
I KNOW.

00:06.607 --> 00:08.141
I COULD SHOW MY GRATITUDE

00:08.141 --> 00:09.977
BY TAKING YOU OUT
TO DINNER SOMETIME.

00:09.977 --> 00:13.013
I WAS THINKING YOU MIGHT BENEFIT
FROM A TRIP TO SAGE CREEK.

00:13.013 --> 00:15.249
SAGE CREEK?
THAT'S A LOONEY BIN.

00:15.249 --> 00:16.517
SLASH HEALTH RESORT.

00:16.517 --> 00:18.118
GOODBYE, MY DARLING.

00:18.118 --> 00:20.387
HOW SOON UNTIL WE GO IN
AND TAKE OFF OUR CLOTHES?

00:20.387 --> 00:22.656
WE SHOULD WAIT UNTIL HIS CAR
LEAVES THE DRIVEWAY.

00:22.656 --> 00:26.260
YOU'RE...SUPER-COOL
AND REALLY NICE.

00:26.260 --> 00:27.628
NOTHING ABOUT MY LOOKS?

00:27.628 --> 00:29.997
YOU'RE MY HERO.

00:29.997 --> 00:34.568
♪ PROMISE ME YOU'LL STAY ♪

00:34.568 --> 00:36.370
SHE'S PERFECT.

00:36.370 --> 00:38.272
I REALLY LIKE YOU.

00:38.272 --> 00:40.007
AND I LIKE YOU.

00:40.007 --> 00:42.142
AND YOU MAKE ME
FEEL GOOD ABOUT MYSELF.

00:42.142 --> 00:44.511
I'VE BEEN NEEDING SOMEONE
TO DO THAT.

00:44.511 --> 00:45.746
DOES HE TREAT YOU WELL?

00:45.746 --> 00:48.115
ETHAN IS GREAT.
GOOD.

00:48.115 --> 00:49.616
YOU DESERVE THE BEST.

00:49.616 --> 00:51.485
THIS MUST REALLY BURN --

00:51.485 --> 00:54.021
RICH KID
LOSING TO THE POOL BOY.

00:54.021 --> 00:56.256
YOU SEEM KIND OF OBSESSED
WITH OTHER PEOPLE'S MONEY.

00:56.256 --> 00:58.292
HEY, I GOT WHAT I WANT.

00:58.292 --> 01:00.260
I KNOW
DAHLIA HAD AN AFFAIR!

01:00.260 --> 01:02.095
WHO WAS IT WITH?!

01:04.131 --> 01:05.566
OPAL HAS BEEN
SO NASTY TO YOU.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.367
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO
BRING HER CLOTHES?

01:07.367 --> 01:09.503
EVEN BITCHES NEED SOMETHING
TO WEAR HOME FROM THE HOSPITAL.

01:09.503 --> 01:10.737
Carmen:
IT'S A PICTURE OF A BLONDE.

01:10.737 --> 01:13.407
THAT'S DAHLIA.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.075
IF OPAL
HAD AN AFFAIR WITH DAHLIA,

01:15.075 --> 01:17.144
NO WONDER
NICK IS SO UNCOMFORTABLE.

01:17.144 --> 01:19.980
IF NICK KNOWS HIS WIFE
AND HIS MAID WERE LOVERS...

01:19.980 --> 01:21.415
WHY IS SHE STILL
WORKING HERE?

01:21.415 --> 01:23.016
DID YOU TALK TO NICK
ABOUT OPAL

01:23.016 --> 01:24.551
AND HER DRAWER
OF MANY SECRETS?

01:24.551 --> 01:27.187
FROM NOW ON, I PLAY THIS GAME
THE WAY SHE DOES --

01:27.187 --> 01:29.656
WITH MY EYES OPEN,
MY MOUTH SHUT,

01:29.656 --> 01:31.658
AND MY CLAWS
BEHIND MY BACK.

01:32.993 --> 01:34.194
[ GASPS ]

01:40.434 --> 01:41.969
Marisol:
GOOD MORNING, OPAL.

01:41.969 --> 01:43.003
MORNING.

01:43.003 --> 01:45.372
WHEN DOES NICHOLAS
GET BACK?

01:45.372 --> 01:47.074
TOMORROW.

01:47.074 --> 01:48.976
9:53.

01:48.976 --> 01:50.744
YOU SOUND EAGER
TO HAVE HIM BACK.

01:50.744 --> 01:52.212
I AM.

01:52.212 --> 01:54.247
WE HAVE LOTS TO TALK ABOUT.

01:54.247 --> 01:57.317
I'M SURE.

01:57.317 --> 01:59.252
COFFEE?

01:59.252 --> 02:01.421
SMELLS WONDERFUL.

02:01.421 --> 02:04.358
IT'S A NEW BLEND
I'M EXPERIMENTING WITH.

02:04.358 --> 02:06.393
BEFORE I FORGET,

02:06.393 --> 02:08.729
THANKS FOR TAKING MY THINGS
TO THE HOSPITAL.

02:08.729 --> 02:10.731
NO BIG DEAL.
YES, WELL...

02:10.731 --> 02:13.400
WHEN YOU WERE IN MY ROOM,

02:13.400 --> 02:15.969
DID YOU HAPPEN TO OPEN
THE TOP DRAWER OF MY BUREAU?

02:15.969 --> 02:17.004
EXCUSE ME?

02:17.004 --> 02:18.572
I USUALLY KEEP IT LOCKED.

02:18.572 --> 02:19.973
HUH.

02:19.973 --> 02:22.209
I DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

02:22.209 --> 02:24.645
WHY?

02:24.645 --> 02:26.013
WHAT'S IN THAT DRAWER?

02:26.013 --> 02:29.650
THINGS. PRIVATE THINGS.

02:29.650 --> 02:33.754
WELL, MAYBE YOU
LEFT IT UNLOCKED BY ACCIDENT.

02:35.522 --> 02:37.991
PERHAPS.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.460
BUT IF
SOMEONE WAS IN THERE,

02:40.460 --> 02:42.396
I'D BE VERY ANGRY.

02:42.396 --> 02:44.064
OF COURSE.

02:44.064 --> 02:46.533
PEOPLE NEED TO FEEL COMFORTABLE
IN THEIR OWN HOMES.

02:46.533 --> 02:48.502
WELL, THEN...

02:48.502 --> 02:50.704
ENJOY THE COFFEE.

03:09.723 --> 03:11.425
HEY.

03:11.425 --> 03:12.659
MORNING, VALENTINA.

03:12.659 --> 03:13.727
WHERE ARE YOU OFF TO?

03:13.727 --> 03:15.262
THE GROCERY STORE.

03:15.262 --> 03:17.764
COULD YOU
SWING BY NEIMAN'S?

03:17.764 --> 03:20.100
I NEED
ANOTHER JAR OF MOISTURIZER.

03:20.100 --> 03:22.202
UH, THIS SHOULD COVER IT.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.970
$300?

03:23.970 --> 03:25.439
WHY SO EXPENSIVE?

03:25.439 --> 03:28.241
THE MAIN INGREDIENT
IS NIGHTINGALE DROPPINGS.

03:28.241 --> 03:29.710
AND YOU PAY EXTRA FOR THAT?

03:29.710 --> 03:32.512
IT IS WORTH IT. IT HELPS MY SKIN
LOOK 10 YEARS YOUNGER.

03:32.512 --> 03:34.581
SO WHY DON'T YOU USE IT
ON YOUR HANDS?

03:34.581 --> 03:37.384
I DO.

03:37.384 --> 03:38.585
PLEASE GO.

03:38.585 --> 03:41.021
SEE YOU
IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.

03:45.759 --> 03:49.229
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

03:53.266 --> 03:55.335
REMI,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:55.335 --> 03:57.738
CAN'T I BRING FLOWERS
TO A PRETTY GIRL?

03:57.738 --> 03:59.673
NOT WHEN
SHE'S DATING SOMEONE ELSE.

03:59.673 --> 04:01.508
FRIENDS GIVE EACH OTHER
STUFF, AND...

04:01.508 --> 04:03.510
WE ARE STILL FRIENDS,
RIGHT?

04:03.510 --> 04:05.979
OF COURSE WE ARE.

04:05.979 --> 04:08.181
BY THE WAY, I MET ETHAN.

04:08.181 --> 04:09.249
YOU DID?

04:09.249 --> 04:11.017
YEAH, WE HAD
AN INTERESTING TALK.

04:11.017 --> 04:12.519
YOU KNOW,
I'VE GOT TO BE HONEST...

04:12.519 --> 04:14.654
[ SIGHS ] DOESN'T
SEEM LIKE SUCH A GOOD GUY.

04:14.654 --> 04:16.389
IS THAT
WHY YOU CAME HERE?!

04:16.389 --> 04:17.991
TO INSULT
MY NEW BOYFRIEND?!

04:17.991 --> 04:19.359
I'M JUST
LOOKING OUT FOR YOU.

04:19.359 --> 04:20.460
I MEAN, HOW WELL
DO YOU EVEN KNOW THIS GUY?

04:20.460 --> 04:23.263
I KNOW THAT'S HE'S SWEET...

04:23.263 --> 04:24.998
AND FUNNY...

04:24.998 --> 04:27.634
AND HE GETS ME
IN A WAY THAT YOU DON'T.

04:27.634 --> 04:29.369
COME ON. I GET YOU.

04:29.369 --> 04:31.371
ETHAN'S MOM IS A MAID,
JUST LIKE MINE.

04:31.371 --> 04:32.639
HE KNOWS WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO GROW UP

04:32.639 --> 04:34.241
WANTING
WHAT YOU CAN'T HAVE.

04:34.241 --> 04:36.743
TRUST ME. I'VE LEARNED
WHAT THAT FEELS LIKE.

04:36.743 --> 04:39.146
THANK YOU FOR THE FLOWERS.

04:39.146 --> 04:41.748
BUT DON'T COME HERE
UNANNOUNCED.

05:00.534 --> 05:01.968
[ GASPS ]

05:01.968 --> 05:04.237
[ MOANING ]

05:13.380 --> 05:16.016
STOP RIGHT THERE!

05:16.016 --> 05:18.985
DO YOU REALLY THINK I'M
GONNA LET YOU WALK IN HERE
WITH THOSE DIRTY BOOTS?

05:18.985 --> 05:21.988
HOW ELSE
CAN I GIVE YOU...

05:21.988 --> 05:23.256
YOUR PRESENT?

05:23.256 --> 05:25.125
YOU MAY ENTER.

05:25.125 --> 05:26.259
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:26.259 --> 05:28.061
Carmen:
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

05:28.061 --> 05:30.197
IT'S JUST
A "THANK YOU" GIFT.

05:30.197 --> 05:32.399
EVER SINCE I CAME HERE,
YOU'VE BEEN SO NICE TO ME...

05:32.399 --> 05:34.634
IF I KNEW THERE WERE PRESENT
I WOULD HAVE BEEN NICER.

05:34.634 --> 05:35.969
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:35.969 --> 05:37.971
[ GASPS ]
[ LID CLATTERS ]

05:37.971 --> 05:40.407
<i>iAVE MARIA PURíSIMA!</i>

05:40.407 --> 05:42.108
DO YOU LIKE IT?

05:42.108 --> 05:45.178
LIKE IT?
I WANT TO BE BURIED IN IT.

05:45.178 --> 05:46.713
BUT...

05:46.713 --> 05:49.249
I CAN'T TAKE THIS.

05:49.249 --> 05:51.651
WHY NOT?
TY...

05:51.651 --> 05:54.020
IT LOOKS EXPENSIVE.

05:54.020 --> 05:56.022
WOULD YOU PREFER
A CHEAPER GIFT?

05:56.022 --> 05:57.557
STOP TRYING TO TRICK ME.

05:57.557 --> 05:59.259
YOU'VE MADE A HUGE DIFFERENCE
IN MY LIFE.

05:59.259 --> 06:01.428
SO, PLEASE,
JUST TRY IT ON.

06:03.396 --> 06:05.632
WELL,
MAYBE JUST A SLEEVE.

06:08.368 --> 06:11.171
OKAY, THE OTHER ONE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:12.272 --> 06:15.075
OH, MY GOD.

06:15.075 --> 06:16.276
OHH.

06:16.276 --> 06:18.378
OH, NO!
NOW I'VE GOT A PROBLEM.

06:18.378 --> 06:19.579
WHAT'S THAT?

06:19.579 --> 06:21.014
I'M NEVER
TAKING THIS JACKET OFF,

06:21.014 --> 06:22.983
AND I STILL
GOT FLOORS TO MOP.

06:22.983 --> 06:24.217
[ LAUGHS ]

06:27.988 --> 06:29.522
THANK YOU.
MM-HMM.

06:29.522 --> 06:30.757
SO,
LET ME ASK YOU THIS...

06:30.757 --> 06:32.425
AS A PROFESSIONAL CHEF,

06:32.425 --> 06:34.494
IS IT HARD TO EAT
AT SOMEONE ELSE'S RESTAURANT?

06:34.494 --> 06:35.662
NAH.

06:35.662 --> 06:37.664
IF THE FOOD'S GOOD,
I HAVE A GREAT TIME.

06:37.664 --> 06:40.166
AND IF IT'S NOT,
I'M HAPPY THE COMPETITION SUCKS.

06:40.166 --> 06:41.534
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

06:41.534 --> 06:43.236
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
AS A PROFESSIONAL HOUSEKEEPER,

06:43.236 --> 06:45.505
DO YOU JUDGE THE CLEANLINESS
OF EVERYBODY'S HOUSE?

06:45.505 --> 06:48.208
NOT ALWAYS.

06:48.208 --> 06:50.477
BUT EVERY NOW AND THEN...

06:50.477 --> 06:52.712
WHAT?

06:52.712 --> 06:54.481
JAVIER,
YOU HAVE A LOVELY HOME.

06:54.481 --> 06:56.516
IT'S WARM AND INVITING...

06:56.516 --> 06:57.984
AND COVERED IN DIRT.

06:57.984 --> 06:59.286
YOU NEED A MAID.

06:59.286 --> 07:01.021
I HAVE A MAID.

07:01.021 --> 07:03.290
YOU LIE.
IT'S TRUE.

07:03.290 --> 07:04.624
CONCEPCION WAS HERE TODAY.

07:04.624 --> 07:07.027
WELL, THEN
I FEEL I MUST ASK YOU,

07:07.027 --> 07:08.695
IS SHE LEGALLY BLIND?

07:08.695 --> 07:10.530
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:10.530 --> 07:13.400
I KNOW SHE'S NOT THE GREATEST
CLEANING LADY IN THE WORLD,

07:13.400 --> 07:15.635
BUT SHE'S BEEN WITH ME
FOR 10 YEARS.

07:15.635 --> 07:16.970
SHE'S VERY LOYAL.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.538
YOU WANT LOYAL?
GET A DOG.

07:18.538 --> 07:20.473
YOU WANT A CLEAN HOUSE?
GET A REAL MAID.

07:20.473 --> 07:22.242
YOU'RE KIND OF A HARD-ASS.

07:22.242 --> 07:23.677
IF ONE OF THE COOKS
IN YOUR KITCHEN

07:23.677 --> 07:25.512
KEPT BURNING THE FOOD,
WOULD YOU KEEP THEM?

07:25.512 --> 07:27.113
YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.349
I'LL ASK CONCEPCION
TO STEP UP HER GAME.

07:29.349 --> 07:30.984
DON'T ASK. TELL.

07:30.984 --> 07:32.419
THREATEN TO FIRE HER
IF YOU HAVE TO.

07:32.419 --> 07:35.622
[ Chuckling ] OKAY. OKAY.

07:35.622 --> 07:37.657
YOU REALLY THINK
IT'S THAT BAD?

07:37.657 --> 07:40.560
I DO. I REALLY DO.

07:40.560 --> 07:42.195
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

07:45.999 --> 07:47.434
Nurse: MR. POWELL?

07:47.434 --> 07:49.970
IT'S TIME FOR
YOUR MEDS.

07:51.237 --> 07:53.974
AH, THE BLUE ONES --
MY FAVORITE.

07:53.974 --> 07:56.376
FAREWELL, AFTERNOON.

07:56.376 --> 07:58.979
[ SIGHS ]

07:58.979 --> 08:01.014
OH, AND THAT'S FOR YOU.

08:01.014 --> 08:03.049
I'M A NURSE,
NOT A WAITRESS.

08:03.049 --> 08:05.151
GO AHEAD. TAKE IT.

08:05.151 --> 08:08.121
BUY YOURSELF
SOME SHOES THAT DON'T SQUEAK.

08:11.124 --> 08:12.559
MR. POWELL?

08:12.559 --> 08:14.094
VALENTINA!

08:14.094 --> 08:15.729
DID YOU BRING MY BOOKS?
GOT THEM RIGHT HERE.

08:17.530 --> 08:20.133
Did you bring
the other thing?

08:20.133 --> 08:21.267
Slip it to me,
slip it to me.

08:24.637 --> 08:26.406
GLORIOUS!

08:26.406 --> 08:28.241
WHY DO I HAVE TO
SNEAK THESE IN?

08:28.241 --> 08:29.509
THEY'RE JUST COOKIES.

08:29.509 --> 08:32.112
MY NURSE WON'T ALLOW
PROCESSED SUGAR HERE.

08:32.112 --> 08:35.715
THOUGH SHE CERTAINLY
SEEMS TO ENJOY IT AT HOME.

08:35.715 --> 08:38.084
SO...
YOU LOOK RELAXED.

08:38.084 --> 08:39.419
HOW COULD I NOT?

08:39.419 --> 08:41.187
I GET MASSAGES
EVERY MORNING,

08:41.187 --> 08:43.690
LOTS OF COLORFUL SEDATIVES
EVERY AFTERNOON.

08:43.690 --> 08:45.658
IF I HAD KNOWN
HOW MUCH FUN THIS WAS,

08:45.658 --> 08:47.727
I WOULD HAVE HAD
A NERVOUS BREAKDOWN AGES AGO.

08:49.195 --> 08:51.164
SO, WHY DIDN'T EVELYN COME?

08:51.164 --> 08:53.533
WELL...
SHE COULDN'T GET AWAY.

08:53.533 --> 08:56.102
THINGS ARE CRAZY BACK HOME.

08:56.102 --> 08:57.537
IS TONY HELPING OUT?

08:57.537 --> 08:59.139
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
ON TOP OF THINGS.

08:59.139 --> 09:01.007
OH, HE IS.

09:03.643 --> 09:05.412
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

09:05.412 --> 09:07.347
I WAS JUST THINKING...

09:07.347 --> 09:09.115
IT WOULD BE GREAT
IF YOU CAME BACK HOME.

09:09.115 --> 09:10.283
THAT'S SWEET.

09:10.283 --> 09:12.018
I'M NOT QUITE READY YET.

09:12.018 --> 09:13.720
ARE YOU SURE?

09:13.720 --> 09:16.389
'CAUSE
MRS. POWELL MISSES YOU.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.324
MORE THAN SHE KNOWS.

09:20.393 --> 09:22.195
WHAT AN ODD THING TO SAY.

09:24.564 --> 09:28.635
IT WAS NICE TO SEE YOU,
BUT I HAVE TO GET BACK.

09:28.635 --> 09:30.737
ENJOY YOUR BOOKS.

09:45.552 --> 09:47.120
ROSIE.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.655
[ GASPS ]

09:48.655 --> 09:50.256
SPENCE.

09:50.256 --> 09:52.525
I WAS JUST
HAVING DINNER WITH MY LAWYER.

09:52.525 --> 09:54.327
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

09:54.327 --> 09:55.995
GOOD.

09:55.995 --> 09:58.565
YOU HAVE A MINUTE?
I NEED TO EXPLAIN SOME THINGS.

09:58.565 --> 10:00.567
ACTUALLY,
I'M HERE WITH SOMEONE.

10:02.001 --> 10:03.636
DIDN'T REALIZE
WE HAD COMPANY.

10:03.636 --> 10:05.271
OH.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.573
I'M REGGIE.

10:06.573 --> 10:08.508
SPENCE WESTMORE.

10:10.110 --> 10:11.277
OH, UH...

10:11.277 --> 10:13.179
SPENCE IS
THE MAN I USED TO WORK FOR.

10:13.179 --> 10:14.414
OH.

10:14.414 --> 10:17.150
AND REGGIE IS MY...

10:17.150 --> 10:19.719
IMMIGRATION LAWYER.

10:19.719 --> 10:21.421
OH.

10:23.389 --> 10:26.426
WELL...
THANKS FOR STOPPING BY.

10:40.673 --> 10:43.143
WOULD YOU LIKE A DRINK?

10:43.143 --> 10:46.045
NO, THANKS.

10:46.045 --> 10:48.515
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:48.515 --> 10:50.550
YOU WERE
SO QUIET IN THE CAR.

10:50.550 --> 10:52.385
JUST TRYING TO
FIGURE OUT WHERE I STAND.

10:52.385 --> 10:54.687
IN THE DINING ROOM?

10:54.687 --> 10:56.356
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:56.356 --> 10:57.690
WHERE I STAND WITH YOU.

10:57.690 --> 11:00.193
W-WE'VE BEEN DATING
FOR A WHILE NOW.

11:00.193 --> 11:02.395
I THOUGHT I WAS MORE THAN JUST
YOUR "IMMIGRATION LAWYER."

11:02.395 --> 11:04.264
OF COURSE YOU ARE.

11:04.264 --> 11:08.034
BUT THIS THING
HAS BEEN MOVING SO SLOW.

11:08.034 --> 11:10.403
NOW I'M STARTING TO THINK,
IS IT BECAUSE OF THAT GUY?

11:10.403 --> 11:12.972
SPENCE AND I WERE...
TOGETHER.

11:12.972 --> 11:15.008
BUT IT ENDED A WHILE AGO.

11:15.008 --> 11:17.744
NOW HE'S GOING THROUGH
A BAD DIVORCE.

11:17.744 --> 11:19.379
OH.

11:19.379 --> 11:23.082
AND I COULDN'T TELL HIM
I'M DATING SUCH A WONDERFUL MAN,

11:23.082 --> 11:25.985
ESPECIALLY
NOW THAT HE'S ALL ALONE.

11:25.985 --> 11:27.987
YOU THINK I'M WONDERFUL?

11:27.987 --> 11:29.689
OF COURSE.

11:34.994 --> 11:36.596
SO, YOU AND SPENCE...

11:36.596 --> 11:38.131
WAS IT SERIOUS?

11:38.131 --> 11:39.666
WELL...

11:39.666 --> 11:42.035
HE DID
ASK ME TO MARRY HIM.

11:44.304 --> 11:46.739
I THINK
I'LL TAKE THAT DRINK NOW.

11:51.511 --> 11:53.746
[ VACUUM WHIRRING ]

11:55.582 --> 11:57.483
OH, HEY.

11:57.483 --> 11:59.252
YOU WANT TO READ?
I CAN GO CLEAN IN THE DEN.

11:59.252 --> 12:01.688
OH, YEAH.
THAT WOULD BE GREAT. THANKS.

12:01.688 --> 12:04.224
[ VACUUM SHUTS OFF ]

12:04.224 --> 12:06.259
HEY.

12:06.259 --> 12:08.328
WHOSE JACKET?
MINE.

12:08.328 --> 12:10.330
HANDS OFF!
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:10.330 --> 12:12.498
WOW.
AM I PAYING YOU TOO MUCH,

12:12.498 --> 12:14.100
OR ARE YOU STEALING FROM ME?

12:14.100 --> 12:15.435
IT WAS A GIFT.

12:15.435 --> 12:17.303
AND YOU ARE DEFINITELY NOT
PAYING ME TOO MUCH.

12:17.303 --> 12:19.505
SOMEONE GAVE YOU
A $3,000 JACKET?

12:19.505 --> 12:21.374
IT'S $3,000?!

12:21.374 --> 12:22.976
YEAH, IT'S A YANG LI.

12:22.976 --> 12:24.477
PERI USED TO BUY THOSE
WHEN SHE WAS MAD AT ME.

12:24.477 --> 12:26.379
[ SIGHS ]
SHE HAS A LOT OF THEM.

12:26.379 --> 12:28.414
WOW.
SO...

12:28.414 --> 12:30.083
WHO'S YOUR SUGAR DADDY?

12:30.083 --> 12:32.252
UH...

12:32.252 --> 12:33.386
YOUR NEPHEW.

12:33.386 --> 12:35.388
TY IS 17!

12:35.388 --> 12:37.123
WHY WOULD YOU
ACCEPT A GIFT LIKE THIS?

12:37.123 --> 12:38.524
I DON'T KNOW!

12:38.524 --> 12:41.160
HE SAID SOMETHING ABOUT
HELPING HIM OUT OF A DARK PLACE,

12:41.160 --> 12:43.463
AND I WASN'T REALLY LISTENING.
I WAS LOOKING AT THE JACKET!

12:43.463 --> 12:46.266
HE PROBABLY PAID FOR IT
WITH HIS MOTHER'S CREDIT CARD.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.368
YOU WANT ME TO
SEND HER A THANK-YOU CARD?

12:48.368 --> 12:49.669
I WANT YOU TO GIVE IT BACK.

12:49.669 --> 12:51.504
BUT I LOVE THIS JACKET!

12:51.504 --> 12:53.273
I DON'T CARE!

12:53.273 --> 12:55.508
[ SIGHS ] FINE!

12:55.508 --> 12:59.178
BUT IF I EVER <i>DO</i> STEAL FROM YOU,
THIS WILL BE THE REASON.

13:11.224 --> 13:13.259
HEY.

13:13.259 --> 13:15.261
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT ETHAN?

13:15.261 --> 13:16.763
I BARELY KNOW HIM.

13:16.763 --> 13:18.398
WHY?

13:18.398 --> 13:20.066
WELL, I HAD A RUN-IN
WITH HIM THE OTHER DAY,

13:20.066 --> 13:22.368
AND I GOT THIS...
WEIRD VIBE.

13:22.368 --> 13:24.003
HE'S DATING YOUR EX.

13:24.003 --> 13:26.139
THINK THAT MIGHT'VE
COLORED YOUR OPINION?

13:26.139 --> 13:27.640
NO, I SWEAR.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.475
I TRIED TO GIVE HIM
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT,

13:29.475 --> 13:31.511
BUT SOMETHING ABOUT HIM...

13:31.511 --> 13:34.013
THEN I TRIED TO WARN
VALENTINA, BUT SHE JUST
GOT ANGRY WITH ME.

13:34.013 --> 13:36.983
[ SIGHS ]
WELCOME TO MY WORLD.

13:36.983 --> 13:39.552
SO, WHAT SHOULD I DO?

13:39.552 --> 13:42.422
I PROMISED VALENTINA
I WOULDN'T MEDDLE IN HER LIFE.

13:42.422 --> 13:43.690
OH.

13:43.690 --> 13:47.026
[ SIGHS ]

13:47.026 --> 13:49.662
BUT IF I WERE
FREE TO GIVE ADVICE,

13:49.662 --> 13:51.431
IT WOULD SOUND
SOMETHING LIKE THIS --

13:51.431 --> 13:53.266
IF YOU WANT VALENTINA BACK,

13:53.266 --> 13:56.102
YOU CAN'T TELL HER
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ETHAN.

13:56.102 --> 13:59.339
YOU HAVE TO REMIND HER
OF WHAT'S RIGHT WITH YOU.

14:01.240 --> 14:02.608
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:02.608 --> 14:04.544
THAT'S THE BEST ADVICE
I NEVER GOT.

14:04.544 --> 14:06.546
I'M GLAD.

14:06.546 --> 14:08.247
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW...

14:08.247 --> 14:10.650
I'M ROOTING FOR YOU.

14:19.726 --> 14:21.394
HEY, BEAUTIFUL.

14:21.394 --> 14:23.196
HEY.

14:28.301 --> 14:29.635
WE HAVE TO TALK.

14:29.635 --> 14:31.504
I WAS HOPING TO UNPACK,
MAYBE GO FOR A RUN.

14:31.504 --> 14:32.472
CAN IT WAIT?

14:34.374 --> 14:36.075
NO. IT CAN'T.

14:44.384 --> 14:47.353
I KNOW DAHLIA'S AFFAIR
WAS WITH OPAL.

14:49.389 --> 14:51.391
WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

14:51.391 --> 14:53.126
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

14:53.126 --> 14:55.128
WHAT I WANT TO KNOW IS
WHY <i>YOU</i> DIDN'T TELL ME.

14:55.128 --> 14:58.364
[ SIGHS ] IT WAS
A HUMILIATING DISCOVERY.

14:58.364 --> 15:00.099
I DON'T LIKE TO DISCUSS IT.

15:00.099 --> 15:02.502
NO, YOU DON'T
LIKE TO DISCUSS IT

15:02.502 --> 15:04.737
BECAUSE IT RAISES
AN OBVIOUS QUESTION.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.640
WHICH IS?
WHY IS
YOUR DEAD WIFE'S LOVER

15:07.640 --> 15:09.642
STILL LIVING
IN YOUR HOUSE?!

15:09.642 --> 15:12.712
LOOK...

15:12.712 --> 15:16.649
OUR MARRIAGE
WAS FAR FROM PERFECT.

15:16.649 --> 15:19.285
BUT I LOVED DAHLIA.

15:19.285 --> 15:22.088
WHEN SHE DIED,
I WAS DEVASTATED.

15:23.389 --> 15:24.690
SO WAS OPAL.

15:24.690 --> 15:28.127
I KNOW IT SOUNDS STRANGE,
BUT...

15:28.127 --> 15:29.729
WE HELPED EACH OTHER
GET THROUGH IT.

15:32.131 --> 15:33.666
IT WAS A BAD TIME.

15:33.666 --> 15:35.168
I GET IT.

15:38.004 --> 15:39.972
BUT'S IT'S BEEN 15 YEARS.

15:39.972 --> 15:43.276
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S TIME
TO SEND OPAL ON HER MERRY WAY?

15:45.411 --> 15:47.380
BUT SHE'S
SUCH A GOOD HOUSEKEEPER.

15:47.380 --> 15:49.982
WHEN SOMEONE
MAKES YOU FEEL UNWELCOME

15:49.982 --> 15:52.385
AND CREEPED OUT
IN YOUR OWN HOUSE,

15:52.385 --> 15:54.654
THEY'RE NOT
GOOD AT THEIR JOB!

15:54.654 --> 15:57.490
MARISOL...
NO! I'M SERIOUS!

15:57.490 --> 16:02.395
I CAN NO LONGER LIVE UNDER
THE SAME ROOF AS THAT WOMAN!

16:03.996 --> 16:05.264
OKAY.

16:05.264 --> 16:07.166
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

16:10.102 --> 16:13.573
EVERYTHING
IS GONNA BE FINE.

16:29.279 --> 16:31.381
OKAY.
I KNOW THIS CROISSANT

16:31.381 --> 16:33.116
LOOKS BIG ENOUGH
TO FEED FOUR PEOPLE,

16:33.116 --> 16:35.952
BUT I AM NOT SHARING.

16:35.952 --> 16:37.520
SORRY.

16:37.520 --> 16:38.988
WHAT'S GOING ON?

16:38.988 --> 16:40.857
THIS IS
MY FRIEND FROM CHURCH.

16:40.857 --> 16:42.492
SHE'S HAVING
A TERRIBLE DAY.

16:42.492 --> 16:44.961
HER BOSS
THREATENED TO FIRE HER.

16:44.961 --> 16:48.331
<i>BANDITO.</i>
POOR CONCEPCION.

16:48.331 --> 16:50.100
[ Muffled ] CONCEPCION?

16:50.100 --> 16:51.267
[ SNIFFLES ]

16:52.969 --> 16:54.571
WHAT IS IT
SHE DOES FOR A LIVING?

16:54.571 --> 16:56.473
SAME AS US.
SHE'S A MAID.

16:58.041 --> 16:59.976
I'M...

16:59.976 --> 17:02.145
SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

17:02.145 --> 17:04.848
JAVIER USED TO BE
SUCH A NICE BOSS,

17:04.848 --> 17:08.151
BUT THEN <i>LA PRINCESA</i>
FILLED HIS HEAD WITH LIES.

17:08.151 --> 17:09.552
<i>LA PRINCESA?</i>

17:09.552 --> 17:11.121
HER BOSS'S NEW GIRLFRIEND.

17:11.121 --> 17:12.522
SHE'S A REAL BITCH.

17:12.522 --> 17:14.958
HOW DO WE KNOW THAT?

17:14.958 --> 17:16.426
<i>LA PRINCESA</i> THREW A FIT

17:16.426 --> 17:18.528
BECAUSE THERE WERE TINY WATER
SPOTS ON THE WINE GLASSES.

17:18.528 --> 17:21.030
WELL, MAYBE
THEY WEREN'T SO TINY.

17:22.165 --> 17:23.833
SORRY.

17:23.833 --> 17:24.868
CROISSANT?

17:24.868 --> 17:26.369
I GOT TO GO.

17:26.369 --> 17:28.138
MIGUEL GETS OUT OF SCHOOL
EARLY TODAY.

17:28.138 --> 17:29.439
BYE.

17:30.106 --> 17:31.541
AND SHE'S MY RIDE.

17:31.541 --> 17:34.010
TAKE CARE, CONCEPCION.

17:34.010 --> 17:36.413
AND WE'LL PRAY FOR GOD
TO PUNISH THAT GIRLFRIEND.

17:36.413 --> 17:40.517
OH, DON'T DO THAT.
GOD IS...SO BUSY.

17:40.517 --> 17:43.052
I SHOULD GO, TOO --
JAVIER SAID I HAVE TO SCRUB

17:43.052 --> 17:45.021
EVERY INCH OF
THE HOUSE BY TOMORROW,

17:45.021 --> 17:47.524
OR I AM FIRED.

17:47.524 --> 17:49.492
[ SOBBING ]

17:49.492 --> 17:52.495
W-WHAT'S WRONG NOW?

17:52.495 --> 17:55.865
I WANTED TO GO
TO SAN DIEGO TOMORROW.

17:55.865 --> 17:58.268
HEY, PRIORITIES!

17:58.268 --> 18:01.438
I MEAN, YOUR JOB IS MORE
IMPORTANT THAN SOME VACATION.

18:01.438 --> 18:03.506
I WAS GOING
TO SEE MY GRANDMOTHER!

18:03.506 --> 18:05.108
SHE'S DYING!

18:05.108 --> 18:07.243
WELL, THAT'S NOT GOOD.

18:07.243 --> 18:08.611
[ SOBS ] MAYBE --

18:08.611 --> 18:11.114
MAYBE SHE CAN
HOLD ON FOR ONE MORE DAY.

18:11.114 --> 18:12.882
NO, NO.

18:12.882 --> 18:14.517
YOU NEED TO BE WITH HER.

18:14.517 --> 18:16.886
BUT WHO'S GONNA
CLEAN THE HOUSE?

18:19.055 --> 18:20.423
GIVE ME YOUR KEY.

18:26.496 --> 18:28.164
Valentina:
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

18:28.164 --> 18:30.333
DID YOU DROP THE BOOKS OFF
FOR MR. POWELL?

18:30.333 --> 18:31.968
I DID.

18:31.968 --> 18:33.436
HE ASKED ABOUT YOU.

18:33.436 --> 18:35.405
AWW.

18:37.841 --> 18:40.376
YOU MUST BE VERY HAPPY.

18:43.012 --> 18:44.113
ARE YOU TALKING TO ME?

18:46.516 --> 18:49.886
HE LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.

18:52.188 --> 18:54.157
AT SOME POINT, I MUST HAVE
GIVEN YOU THE IMPRESSION

18:54.157 --> 18:56.125
I ENJOY
SMALL TALK WITH THE HELP.

18:56.125 --> 18:58.027
AND THAT'S NOT THE CASE.

18:58.027 --> 19:00.530
WILL YOU PLEASE
ACCEPT MY APOLOGY

19:00.530 --> 19:03.066
AS YOU LEAVE
TO SCRUB MY TOILET?

19:14.110 --> 19:15.912
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:15.912 --> 19:17.280
CARMEN TOLD ME
WHERE YOU WORKED.

19:17.280 --> 19:18.915
I REALLY
NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

19:18.915 --> 19:21.518
YOU'VE GOT THREE MINUTES.

19:26.956 --> 19:29.859
YOU REMEMBER THE DAY
YOU CAME T-TO MY HOUSE?

19:29.859 --> 19:32.228
AND YOU SAID
ALL THOSE TERRIBLE THINGS?

19:32.228 --> 19:33.997
I REMEMBER.

19:33.997 --> 19:35.398
PERI MADE ME
SAY THOSE THINGS.

19:35.398 --> 19:37.000
SHE SAID THAT
IF YOU AND I GOT TOGETHER,

19:37.000 --> 19:38.301
SHE WOULD TAKE MY SON AWAY.

19:38.301 --> 19:40.937
OH.

19:40.937 --> 19:43.306
IT KILLED ME
TO HURT YOU LIKE THAT.

19:43.306 --> 19:45.508
IT TURNS OUT
IT WAS ALL POINTLESS.

19:45.508 --> 19:47.577
PERI'S GONE TO COURT
TO GET SOLE CUSTODY OF TUCKER.

19:47.577 --> 19:51.214
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME THIS BEFORE? I
WOULD HAVE UNDERSTOOD.

19:51.214 --> 19:53.383
I THOUGHT ABOUT
CALLING YOU --
BUT YOU NEVER DID.

19:53.383 --> 19:56.119
AND IT'S BEEN MONTHS!

19:57.987 --> 20:00.123
I'M SO SORRY.

20:00.123 --> 20:03.192
BUT YOU HAVE TO KNOW I --

20:03.192 --> 20:05.261
I NEVER STOPPED LOVING YOU.

20:10.500 --> 20:12.201
REGGIE. HI.

20:12.201 --> 20:13.369
HELLO.

20:14.837 --> 20:16.472
AM I
INTERRUPTING SOMETHING?

20:16.472 --> 20:18.408
NO. NO.
SPENCE WAS JUST LEAVING.

20:18.408 --> 20:21.244
THINK ABOUT WHAT I SAID?

20:29.285 --> 20:31.287
THAT GUY SEEMS TO BE
POPPING UP A LOT LATELY.

20:31.287 --> 20:33.256
HE HAD SOMETHING
HE NEEDED TO TELL ME.

20:33.256 --> 20:35.425
STILL, I'M NOT COMFORTABLE
WITH THE TWO OF YOU
HANGING OUT TOGETHER.

20:37.961 --> 20:41.264
I UNDERSTAND, BUT...

20:41.264 --> 20:43.533
IT'S NOT UP TO YOU
WHO I SEE.

20:54.844 --> 20:57.981
YOU'RE GIVING IT BACK?
WHY?

20:57.981 --> 21:00.583
YOUR UNCLE FEELS
IT'S AN INAPPROPRIATE GIFT.

21:00.583 --> 21:02.852
NO! YOU DESERVE
BEAUTIFUL THINGS.

21:02.852 --> 21:05.355
I DO. I REALLY DO.

21:05.355 --> 21:07.123
BUT...

21:07.123 --> 21:08.524
[ SIGHS ]

21:08.524 --> 21:10.093
WAIT! JUST...

21:10.093 --> 21:11.461
KEEP IT IN YOUR CLOSET.

21:11.461 --> 21:12.962
UNCLE SPENCE
DOESN'T HAVE TO KNOW.

21:12.962 --> 21:14.497
NO! NO, TY!

21:14.497 --> 21:17.834
I CAN NOT ACCEPT
A JACKET THIS EXPENSIVE.

21:17.834 --> 21:20.470
EVEN THOUGH IT GOES WITH
EVERYTHING I OWN.

21:24.107 --> 21:25.842
I'M SORRY ABOUT THIS.

21:25.842 --> 21:26.976
I GUESS I SCREWED UP.

21:26.976 --> 21:28.978
IT'S THE THOUGHT
THAT COUNTS.

21:28.978 --> 21:31.180
AND IT'S NICE TO KNOW
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT ME.

21:31.180 --> 21:33.082
REALLY?

21:33.082 --> 21:34.450
YEAH.

21:34.450 --> 21:36.519
I FEEL THE SAME WAY ABOUT YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:36.519 --> 21:38.254
WOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:38.254 --> 21:41.190
EVERY MORNING,
YOU COME OUT OF YOUR ROOM AND...

21:41.190 --> 21:44.293
YOU SMILE
THAT GOOFY SMILE...

21:44.293 --> 21:46.362
IT MAKES ME HAPPY.

21:46.362 --> 21:48.097
SOMETIMES, AT NIGHT,

21:48.097 --> 21:51.100
I THANK GOD FOR
BRINGING YOU INTO MY LIFE.

21:51.100 --> 21:53.269
AWWW.

21:53.269 --> 21:54.971
SO WHO NEEDS GIFTS?

21:54.971 --> 21:56.606
WE'VE GOT EACH OTHER,
RIGHT?

22:08.851 --> 22:11.454
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
WE WERE GOING HOME.

22:11.454 --> 22:13.122
WE ARE.

22:13.122 --> 22:14.857
SURPRISE!

22:14.857 --> 22:17.026
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

22:17.026 --> 22:18.361
I JUST PUT AN OFFER IN
THIS MORNING.

22:18.361 --> 22:21.364
EIGHT BEDROOMS, SIX BATHS,
5,000 SQUARE FEET.

22:21.364 --> 22:22.832
THINK OF IT
AS AN EARLY WEDDING GIFT.

22:22.832 --> 22:23.833
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:23.833 --> 22:25.234
YOU LIKE IT?

22:25.234 --> 22:27.003
I LIKE
THE HOUSE WE LIVE IN.

22:27.003 --> 22:28.905
WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO
SELL IT?
I'M NOT GOING TO.

22:28.905 --> 22:30.473
OPAL'S GOING TO LIVE THERE --
WITH ETHAN.

22:32.108 --> 22:34.110
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT? YOU SAID
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO

22:34.110 --> 22:35.278
LIVE UNDER THE SAME ROOF
WITH HER ANYMORE.

22:35.278 --> 22:36.846
I WANTED YOU TO FIRE HER,

22:36.846 --> 22:39.182
NOT GIVE HER
A MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR ESTATE!

22:39.182 --> 22:42.218
OKAY, BUT THIS WAY,
EVERYBODY GETS WHAT THEY
WANT AND NOBODY'S UNHAPPY.

22:44.153 --> 22:46.389
WHAT DOES THIS WOMAN HAVE
ON YOU?

22:46.389 --> 22:48.024
NOTHING.

22:48.024 --> 22:50.259
THEN WHY CAN'T YOU
GET HER OUT OF YOUR LIFE?

22:50.259 --> 22:52.261
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S A CONFUSING SITUATION.

22:52.261 --> 22:54.530
NO, IT'S NOT.

22:54.530 --> 22:56.966
EITHER SHE GOES, OR I DO.

22:56.966 --> 22:59.368
I THINK
WE CAN ALL UNDERSTAND THAT.

23:08.478 --> 23:09.979
SO...

23:09.979 --> 23:12.281
DID YOU
GIVE THE JACKET BACK?

23:12.281 --> 23:13.483
I DID.

23:13.483 --> 23:15.451
AND HOW DID TY TAKE IT?

23:15.451 --> 23:17.120
WELL...

23:17.120 --> 23:19.388
HE DECIDED TO GIVE ME
SOMETHING ELSE INSTEAD.

23:19.388 --> 23:21.390
I HOPE YOU SAID NO.

23:21.390 --> 23:23.226
WELL, IT'S HARD TO TALK

23:23.226 --> 23:24.994
WHEN SOMEONE'S TONGUE
IS IN YOUR MOUTH.

23:24.994 --> 23:26.863
HE KISSED YOU?

23:26.863 --> 23:27.830
OH, YEAH.

23:27.830 --> 23:28.965
WHY WOULD HE DO THAT?

23:28.965 --> 23:30.133
[ SCOFFS ]

23:30.133 --> 23:32.068
NOT TO BE CONCEITED, BUT...
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:32.068 --> 23:34.470
I MEAN, WHY WOULD HE THINK
THAT YOU'D BE INTERESTED?

23:34.470 --> 23:36.506
WHEN I GAVE HIM
THE JACKET BACK,

23:36.506 --> 23:38.341
YOU KNOW, I WAS
BEING REALLY NICE TO HIM.

23:38.341 --> 23:39.976
AND HE MISUNDERSTOOD.
I GOT IT.

23:39.976 --> 23:41.277
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

23:41.277 --> 23:43.613
YOU'RE GOING TO BE GENTLE,
RIGHT?
NO!

23:43.613 --> 23:45.314
HE KISSED A WOMAN
OLD ENOUGH TO BE HIS --

23:45.314 --> 23:48.384
MAID! I'M OLD ENOUGH
TO BE HIS MAID!

23:48.384 --> 23:50.052
OH. SORRY.

23:50.052 --> 23:53.055
WHY DON'T I TALK TO TY?

23:53.055 --> 23:54.857
YOU KNOW, I'VE HAD
A LOT OF GUYS HIT ON ME.

23:54.857 --> 23:57.026
I KNOW HOW TO
LET HIM DOWN EASY.
NO, IT HAS TO BE ME.

23:57.026 --> 23:59.362
I'VE GOT TO LAY DOWN THE LAW --
HE'S GOT TO UNDERSTAND

23:59.362 --> 24:01.864
YOU DON'T GO AROUND
KISSING THE HELP.

24:01.864 --> 24:03.966
DOES HE KNOW
YOU HAD A THING WITH ROSIE?

24:03.966 --> 24:07.370
OR YOU COULD
LET HIM DOWN EASY.

24:07.370 --> 24:09.005
THAT'S GOOD, TOO.

24:11.007 --> 24:12.875
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:18.514 --> 24:20.249
MRS. POWELL LET ME IN.

24:20.249 --> 24:23.019
SHE SHOULDN'T HAVE.

24:23.019 --> 24:24.287
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO TALK.

24:24.287 --> 24:26.556
JUST ONE MINUTE.
THEN I'LL GO, I SWEAR.

24:26.556 --> 24:28.991
I'M NOT TAKING
ANY MORE GIFTS FROM YOU.

24:28.991 --> 24:30.893
IT'S JUST A PICTURE,
AND...

24:30.893 --> 24:32.395
I THINK
YOU'LL WANT TO HAVE IT.

24:34.497 --> 24:36.866
OH, MY GOD.
IS THIS...?

24:36.866 --> 24:39.001
THAT CLEARING WE FOUND
IN THE CONGO.

24:39.001 --> 24:41.237
REMEMBER THAT MORNING?
I DO.

24:41.237 --> 24:43.372
YOU HAD JUST PULLED
AN ALL-NIGHTER AT THE CLINIC...

24:43.372 --> 24:44.841
AND YOU CAME TO MEET ME.

24:44.841 --> 24:46.409
BUT I WAS TOO TIRED
TO SLEEP, SO...

24:46.409 --> 24:48.477
SO WE WENT FOR A WALK.

24:51.113 --> 24:54.317
THIS WAS THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
SUNRISE I'D EVER SEEN.

24:55.985 --> 24:58.454
YOU KNOW, I THINK ABOUT
THAT MORNING A LOT.

24:58.454 --> 25:01.390
THE COLOR OF THE SKY,
THE LOOK ON YOUR FACE...

25:01.390 --> 25:04.026
YOU WERE IN AFRICA
FOR MONTHS, BUT...

25:04.026 --> 25:06.495
THAT WAS THE ONLY MOMENT
YOU WERE REALLY HAPPY.

25:06.495 --> 25:09.031
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

25:09.031 --> 25:11.868
BECAUSE I GET YOU, VAL.

25:11.868 --> 25:14.503
I GET
EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU.

25:14.503 --> 25:17.273
I KNOW THAT YOU TILT YOUR HEAD
JUST BEFORE YOU GET ANGRY.

25:17.273 --> 25:20.409
I KNOW THAT YOU RUB YOUR
HANDS TOGETHER TO KEEP
YOURSELF FROM CRYING.

25:20.409 --> 25:22.245
AND I KNOW
YOUR FACE GETS RED

25:22.245 --> 25:23.846
WHEN YOU START TO FEEL THINGS
THAT YOU DON'T WANT TO FEEL.

25:26.382 --> 25:28.417
LIKE NOW.

25:32.121 --> 25:35.057
NONE OF THIS MATTERS.

25:35.057 --> 25:36.492
I'M WITH ETHAN.

25:36.492 --> 25:39.362
I KNOW.

25:39.362 --> 25:41.964
JUST TAKE THIS PHOTO
AS A...

25:41.964 --> 25:43.499
REMINDER OF WHAT WE HAD.

25:43.499 --> 25:46.102
AND JUST KNOW,
IF YOU EVER NEED ME...

25:46.102 --> 25:49.071
I WILL COME RUNNING.

25:57.947 --> 26:00.283
JAVIER? IT'S ME.

26:00.283 --> 26:02.218
WHEN ARE YOU OFF WORK?

26:02.218 --> 26:04.120
I'M IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD
AND THOUGHT I'D PICK YOU UP

26:04.120 --> 26:05.988
AND DRIVE YOU HOME.

26:08.491 --> 26:10.226
5:00?

26:10.226 --> 26:11.827
THAT SOON?

26:11.827 --> 26:15.097
NO, THAT'S GOOD.
THAT'S GOOD.

26:20.002 --> 26:22.271
I GOTTA GO.

26:25.241 --> 26:27.476
[ UP-TEMPO LATIN MUSIC PLAYS ]

26:50.967 --> 26:52.034
[ COUGHS ]

27:13.856 --> 27:15.624
I'M NOT SURE WHY
YOU INSISTED ON PICKING ME UP.

27:15.624 --> 27:18.327
I JUST COULDN'T WAIT
TO SEE YOUR LOVELY FACE.

27:18.327 --> 27:20.329
AW, THAT'S NICE.

27:28.004 --> 27:30.539
WHAT'S WRONG?

27:30.539 --> 27:33.242
S-SOMETHING IS DIFFERENT.

27:33.242 --> 27:34.977
IT'S...

27:34.977 --> 27:38.914
I BELIEVE THE WORD YOU'RE
SEARCHING FOR IS "CLEAN."

27:38.914 --> 27:41.517
IT LOOKS LIKE
SHE WAXED YOUR FLOORS

27:41.517 --> 27:43.152
AND ORGANIZED
YOUR SHELVES.

27:43.152 --> 27:45.221
AND WHAT IS
THAT WONDERFUL SCENT?

27:45.221 --> 27:46.589
SCENT?

27:46.589 --> 27:48.257
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
AHH.

27:48.257 --> 27:50.860
SHE USED LAVENDER.

27:50.860 --> 27:52.261
AS A PROFESSIONAL MAID,

27:52.261 --> 27:55.097
I WOULD GIVE CONCEPCION
AN A-PLUS.

27:55.097 --> 27:59.268
THIS IS PROBABLY THE CLEANEST
YOUR HOUSE HAS EVER BEEN.

27:59.268 --> 28:01.070
YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:01.070 --> 28:03.439
SHE IS SO FIRED.

28:03.439 --> 28:05.141
WHAT?!

28:05.141 --> 28:06.575
I'VE BEEN PAYING THAT WOMAN
GOOD MONEY FOR YEARS,

28:06.575 --> 28:08.344
AND NOW I FIND OUT
SHE'S BEEN PHONING IT IN?!

28:08.344 --> 28:10.613
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
SMELL THE LAVENDER.

28:10.613 --> 28:12.114
I AM SO ANGRY!

28:12.114 --> 28:13.482
TO FIND OUT
SHE CAN CLEAN LIKE THIS?!

28:13.482 --> 28:15.985
IN HER DEFENSE, SHE CAN'T.

28:18.554 --> 28:20.523
WHAT?

28:20.523 --> 28:22.391
I CLEANED THE HOUSE.

28:25.127 --> 28:28.397
I MET HER THROUGH A FRIEND,
AND SHE WAS SO SWEET,

28:28.397 --> 28:31.100
AND HER GRANDMOTHER'S
GOING TO KICK THE BUCKET
IN LIKE FIVE MINUTES,

28:31.100 --> 28:34.403
AND I FELT SO GUILTY,
AND...

28:36.372 --> 28:39.308
HAVE YOU EVER COOKED
WITH A PRICKLY PEAR?

28:39.308 --> 28:41.343
A WHAT?

28:41.343 --> 28:43.379
WE USE IT AT MY RESTAURANT
ALL THE TIME.

28:43.379 --> 28:46.982
ON THE OUTSIDE
IT'S ROUGH AND THORNY,

28:46.982 --> 28:48.884
BUT ON THE INSIDE...

28:48.884 --> 28:50.619
IT'S TENDER...

28:50.619 --> 28:53.122
AND UNBELIEVABLY SWEET.

28:53.122 --> 28:56.859
OH, ARE YOU TRYING TO SAY
THAT I'M A PRICKLY PEAR?

28:56.859 --> 29:00.229
YOU LIKE TO COME OFF
TOUGH AND UNFORGIVING,

29:00.229 --> 29:04.366
BUT YOU HAVE A COMPASSIONATE,
CARING HEART.

29:04.366 --> 29:08.104
AND THAT EXTRAORDINARY
COMBINATION...

29:08.104 --> 29:10.372
TURNS ME ON.

29:14.143 --> 29:16.445
I ALSO CLEANED THE BEDROOM.

29:16.445 --> 29:18.547
YOU WANT TO GO MESS IT UP?

29:18.547 --> 29:20.516
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

29:20.516 --> 29:23.152
OH!
[ LAUGHS ]

29:23.152 --> 29:24.520
WHAT?!

29:24.520 --> 29:27.256
WAIT, PERI THAT CLAIMING
THAT <i>I'M</i> UNFIT?

29:27.256 --> 29:29.024
LISTEN, JEFF.

29:29.024 --> 29:31.093
I DON'T CARE IF WE HAVE TO
FILE AN APPEAL OR COUNTERSUE,

29:31.093 --> 29:33.529
JUST GET MY KID BACK, OKAY?!

29:33.529 --> 29:35.998
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

29:40.870 --> 29:41.971
OH!
HEY, I'M SORRY.

29:41.971 --> 29:44.106
HEY! SPENCE, RIGHT?

29:44.106 --> 29:45.274
IT'S ME -- REGGIE.

29:45.274 --> 29:47.977
YEAH, YEAH.
UH, ROSIE'S LAWYER.

29:47.977 --> 29:49.612
AND HER BOYFRIEND.

29:49.612 --> 29:52.481
S-SHE DIDN'T MENTION THAT?

29:52.481 --> 29:54.416
I THOUGHT YOU GUYS TALKED.

29:54.416 --> 29:56.252
NO, NOT ABOUT THAT.

29:56.252 --> 29:58.120
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT, MAN?
YOU LOOK A LITTLE PALE.

29:58.120 --> 30:01.190
YEAH, I'M JUST HAVING...
A TOUGH DAY.

30:01.190 --> 30:02.858
YEAH, I GET IT.

30:02.858 --> 30:05.060
YOU MUST MISS ROSIE
SOMETHING FIERCE, HUH?

30:06.996 --> 30:08.497
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I DO.

30:08.497 --> 30:10.232
I DON'T BLAME YOU.

30:10.232 --> 30:13.235
[ CHUCKLES ] THAT GIRL'S
GOT SOME SERIOUS SKILLS.

30:13.235 --> 30:15.271
SKILLS?

30:15.271 --> 30:17.439
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

30:17.439 --> 30:20.576
GET HER IN THE SACK,
AND, LIKE, SHE TURNS FREAKY.

30:20.576 --> 30:22.111
COULD YOU NOT
TALK ABOUT ROSIE LIKE THAT?

30:22.111 --> 30:23.412
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S COOL, MAN. YOU KNOW?

30:23.412 --> 30:25.247
THIS IS SOMETHING
WE GET TO BOND OVER.

30:25.247 --> 30:28.117
YOU AND ME...
WE BOTH GOT TO TAP THAT.

30:28.117 --> 30:30.352
[ GRUNTS ]

30:35.124 --> 30:36.959
GET OFF OF ME!
GET OFF OF ME!

30:36.959 --> 30:39.061
GET OFF OF ME!
GET OFF OF ME!

30:41.463 --> 30:44.934
YOU STAY AWAY FROM HER!

30:50.105 --> 30:51.974
Man: YOU OKAY?

30:51.974 --> 30:53.976
THAT DEPENDS.

30:53.976 --> 30:55.377
DID YOU GET ALL THAT?

30:55.377 --> 30:56.946
EVERY FRAME.

30:59.148 --> 31:00.883
THEN I'M GREAT.

31:08.557 --> 31:10.359
WHAT'S THIS?

31:10.359 --> 31:12.361
A SEVERANCE CHECK.

31:12.361 --> 31:15.097
I NEED TO LET YOU GO.

31:15.097 --> 31:17.266
YOU CAN'T.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.235
WE HAVE A DEAL.

31:19.235 --> 31:21.237
I'M CHANGING THE TERMS.

31:21.237 --> 31:23.405
YOU'RE NO LONGER WELCOME
IN THIS HOUSE.

31:24.974 --> 31:27.509
I EARNED THE RIGHT
TO BE HERE.

31:27.509 --> 31:30.379
THE LAST 15 YEARS
WERE A GIFT.

31:30.379 --> 31:33.015
IT'S TIME
FOR BOTH OF US TO MOVE ON.

31:33.015 --> 31:34.483
[ GASPS ]

31:34.483 --> 31:38.220
MARISOL'S BEHIND THIS,
ISN'T SHE?

31:38.220 --> 31:40.856
SHE'S THREATENING TO LEAVE.

31:40.856 --> 31:44.093
I CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.
I LOVE HER.

31:44.093 --> 31:46.962
ENOUGH TO GO TO JAIL?

31:49.098 --> 31:51.600
IF I GO TO JAIL,
I AM TAKING YOU WITH ME.

31:54.169 --> 31:56.939
NOW, THAT IS
MORE THAN GENEROUS.

31:56.939 --> 31:59.041
AND ETHAN'S
STILL IN MY WILL.

31:59.041 --> 32:01.210
HE WON'T GET THAT MONEY
UNTIL YOU'RE DEAD.

32:01.210 --> 32:03.145
IF YOU DON'T DO WHAT I SAY,

32:03.145 --> 32:06.048
I WILL SEE TO IT
HE GETS NOTHING AT ALL.

32:12.488 --> 32:14.189
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

32:16.225 --> 32:18.394
HEY, TY.
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

32:18.394 --> 32:20.329
FOR YOU? ALWAYS.

32:21.497 --> 32:23.232
I'M GOOD.

32:23.232 --> 32:24.967
LOOK, I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT
WHAT HAPPENED YESTERDAY.

32:24.967 --> 32:27.236
ME, TOO.

32:27.236 --> 32:30.239
YEAH. THERE'S SOMETHING
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT.

32:30.239 --> 32:32.241
I KNOW.

32:32.241 --> 32:34.143
YOU'RE WORRIED ABOUT
THE MASSIVE AGE DIFFERENCE.

32:34.143 --> 32:36.145
IT'S NOT THAT MASSIVE!

32:36.145 --> 32:38.213
AND, NO, THAT'S NOT IT.

32:38.213 --> 32:40.849
THE THING IS...

32:40.849 --> 32:42.985
I ALREADY HAVE
A BOYFRIEND.

32:44.386 --> 32:46.255
OH.

32:46.255 --> 32:47.856
WHO IS IT?

32:47.856 --> 32:49.925
HE DOESN'T LIKE ME
TO TALK ABOUT HIM.

32:49.925 --> 32:51.093
WHY?

32:52.895 --> 32:54.163
HE'S A CELEBRITY.

32:54.163 --> 32:56.498
OH.

32:56.498 --> 32:58.000
IS IT SERIOUS?

32:58.000 --> 32:59.034
VERY.

33:04.973 --> 33:07.376
OH, HONEY.

33:07.376 --> 33:10.412
I LIKE YOU. I DO.

33:10.412 --> 33:13.015
AND IF THIS GUY WAS
OUT OF THE PICTURE, WHO KNOWS?

33:13.015 --> 33:14.116
SO THERE'S HOPE?

33:14.116 --> 33:16.251
NO. NO.
THERE'S NO HOPE.

33:16.251 --> 33:17.386
JUST A FEW TEARS,
AND THEN MOVING ON.

33:17.386 --> 33:18.887
THAT'S ALL WE GOT.

33:18.887 --> 33:20.222
OKAY?

33:22.057 --> 33:23.292
CARMEN?

33:25.828 --> 33:26.862
MM-HMM.

33:28.097 --> 33:30.833
THIS GUY
IS REALLY LUCKY TO HAVE YOU.

33:39.108 --> 33:41.043
[ SIGHS ]

33:49.885 --> 33:53.222
VALENTINA, WE'RE BACK!

33:53.222 --> 33:56.959
VALENTINA, PLEASE COME.
I REQUIRE ALCOHOL.

33:56.959 --> 33:58.360
MAYBE
SHE'S AT THE STORE.

34:02.297 --> 34:05.000
HAVE YOU NOTICED
A CHANGE IN HER BEHAVIOR LATELY?

34:05.000 --> 34:07.302
WHAT KIND OF A CHANGE?
AFTER OUR LAST CONVERSATION,

34:07.302 --> 34:09.304
SHE GAVE ME
THIS LOOK OF DISDAIN.

34:09.304 --> 34:11.240
ARE YOU SURE?
I KNOW THAT LOOK.

34:11.240 --> 34:13.208
IT'S THE SAME ONE
I GIVE PEOPLE WHO FLY COACH.

34:13.208 --> 34:15.110
DO YOU THINK THERE'S A CHANCE
SHE KNOWS ABOUT US?

34:15.110 --> 34:17.379
NO. WE'VE BEEN
RIDICULOUSLY DISCREET.

34:17.379 --> 34:20.382
THAT'S TRUE. BUT...

34:20.382 --> 34:22.985
COME ON.
VALENTINA'S OBVIOUSLY NOT HOME,

34:22.985 --> 34:26.922
SO HOW ABOUT I GET YOU DRUNK
AND TOUCH YOU INAPPROPRIATELY?

34:26.922 --> 34:28.857
OH, PLEASE DO.

34:28.857 --> 34:31.226
[ MOANS PASSIONATELY ]

34:31.226 --> 34:33.095
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO, LEAD THE WAY.

34:33.095 --> 34:36.198
WELL, AS YOU KNOW,
THAT IS WHAT I PREFER.

34:36.198 --> 34:38.834
HELLO, THERE.

34:38.834 --> 34:41.103
GUESS WHAT --
MR. POWELL CAME HOME.

34:41.103 --> 34:42.971
YES, I CAN SEE THAT.

34:42.971 --> 34:45.274
DARLING, WHY DIDN'T YOU
CALL AND --

34:45.274 --> 34:47.142
AND WARN US
YOU WERE COMING?

34:47.142 --> 34:48.844
WHERE'S THE FUN IN THAT?

34:48.844 --> 34:50.245
COME GIVE US A KISS.

34:51.580 --> 34:52.948
OH!
[ CHUCKLES ]
